wikipedia_page.main: George Onslow Deane (11 December 1828 – 16 February 1929) was an English cricketer.

response: English died at Higher Ball Farm, Tiverton, Devon, on 5 September 1966. At the time of his death he was the oldest surviving first-class cricketer. He is one of four Hampshire players known to have lived to the age of 100, the others being George Deane, Neil McCorkell and John Manners.
*George Deane, cricketer, was born in Bighton
